課程概述 Course Description
       專門研究神經系統的結構、功能、發育、演化、遺傳學、生物化學、生理學、藥理學及病理學的一門科學。對行為及學習的研究都是神經科學的分支。

•This course intends to introduce the basic neuroscience.
•The course is designed for students without Neuroscience and Biology background.
•The course covers the nervous system, brain function and related diseases.
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
This course intends to introduce the basic neuroscience.The course is designed for students without Neuroscience and Biology background.The course covers the nervous system, brain function and related diseases. 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Neuroscience: Past, Today, and Future2Neurons and Glia (Chapter 2)3The Neural Membrane and Action Potential (Chapter 3, 4)4Synaptic Transmission (Chapter 5)5Neurotransmitter Systems (Chapter 6)6Neural Development	(Chapter 23)7The Structure of the Nervous System (Chapter 7)8Midterm exam (12:00-1:20pm)9The Chemical Sense	(Chapter 8)10The Visual and Auditory Systems (Chapter 10, 11)11The Somatic Sensory System (Chapter 12)12Spinal Control of Movement	(Chapter 13)13Autonomic Nervous System	(Chapter 15)14Cognitive Neuroscience I (Chapter 20)15Cognitive Neuroscience II16Diseased Brain (Chapter 22)17Interdisciplinary Neuroscience: Brain Mind Welfare18Final Exam 

